Just learned about this change which means re-working quite a bit of the commands. 
{quote}
Also, they changed the name of the service for NC and CC in 4.3 for RHEL7: They’re called eucalyptus-node and eucalyptus-cluster now. There are symbolic links so the use of eucalyptus-nc and eucalyptus-cc mostly works, but one area it doesn’t work is this disable/re-enable thing. Best thing is to change all occurrences in the RHEL7 mentions of these 2 services (starting, stopping, disabling, re-enabling). But the names of the services in RHEL6 are unchanged, even in 4.3 (using the “service” command).
I made these updates to https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/wiki/display/BTS/Euca+4.3.0+Upgrade+Documentation%3A+RHEL6+to+RHEL7 , but there are more places in the docs where the service names should be changed.
Lincoln
{quote}
